From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Yogesh Tyagi <yogesh.tyagi@intel.com>
Date: Tue, 10 Jun 2026 16:30:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] clang-tidy: SignalHandlerCheck drop constexpr init lists

GCC 16 rejects these StringRef initializer_list declarations as constexpr
in this context ("modification of <temporary> is not a constant
expression"). They are only used as lookup tables, so constexpr is not
required.

Upstream LLVM resolved this differently on main by changing the lookup
tables to plain constexpr C arrays (constexpr StringRef Foo[]), which is
unavailable for LLVM 15. As LLVM 15 is end-of-life, this is a local
backward-compatibility workaround for building with GCC 16 sysroots.

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [LLVM 15 is EOL; fixed differently on llvm-project main]

Signed-off-by: Yogesh Tyagi <yogesh.tyagi@intel.com>
---
 .../clang-tidy/bugprone/SignalHandlerCheck.cpp         | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/clang-tools-extra/clang-tidy/bugprone/SignalHandlerCheck.cpp b/clang-tools-extra/clang-tidy/bugprone/SignalHandlerCheck.cpp
index e0800fca90d8..2866bd66da2d 100644
--- a/clang-tools-extra/clang-tidy/bugprone/SignalHandlerCheck.cpp
+++ b/clang-tools-extra/clang-tidy/bugprone/SignalHandlerCheck.cpp
@@ -13,7 +13,7 @@
 
 // This is the minimal set of safe functions.
 // https://wiki.sei.cmu.edu/confluence/display/c/SIG30-C.+Call+only+asynchronous-safe+functions+within+signal+handlers
-constexpr std::initializer_list<llvm::StringRef> MinimalConformingFunctions = {
+static const std::initializer_list<llvm::StringRef> MinimalConformingFunctions = {
     "signal", "abort", "_Exit", "quick_exit"};
 
 // The POSIX-defined set of safe functions.
@@ -23,7 +23,7 @@ constexpr std::initializer_list<llvm::StringRef> MinimalConformingFunctions = {
 // mentioned POSIX specification was not updated after 'quick_exit' appeared
 // in the C11 standard.
 // Also, we want to keep the "minimal set" a subset of the "POSIX set".
-constexpr std::initializer_list<llvm::StringRef> POSIXConformingFunctions = {
+static const std::initializer_list<llvm::StringRef> POSIXConformingFunctions = {
     "_Exit",
     "_exit",
     "abort",
-- 
2.34.1
